# Secrets & Environment Variable Operations

## Environment Matrix

Four environments must stay in sync. Use `make env-check` to validate all at once.

| Environment | Source of Truth | How to Update |
|---|---|---|
| **Vercel Production** | Vercel Dashboard / `vercel env ls` | `vercel env add VAR production` or Vercel Dashboard |
| **Studio .env.local** | Pulled from Vercel | `make env-pull` (runs `vercel env pull`) |
| **Hetzner .env** | `/opt/paperwork-ops/.env` on server | SSH: `ssh root@204.168.147.100` then edit `.env` |
| **n8n container** | Inherits from Hetzner `.env` via `compose.yaml` | Add mapping in `compose.yaml`, restart: `docker compose restart n8n` |

## Studio Environment Variables (apps/studio)

### Critical (app breaks without these)

| Variable | Purpose | Vercel | .env.local | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `DATABASE_URL` | Neon PostgreSQL (pooled) | Auto (Neon integration) | Via `env-pull` | Code falls back to `DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED` |
| `SECRETS_ENCRYPTION_KEY` | AES-256-GCM key for secrets vault | Manual | Via `env-pull` | Generate: `openssl rand -base64 32` |
| `ADMIN_EMAILS` | Basic Auth allowed emails | Manual | Via `env-pull` | Comma-separated |
| `ADMIN_ACCESS_PASSWORD` | Basic Auth password | Manual | Via `env-pull` | Dev bypasses auth via NODE_ENV check |

### Important (features degrade without these)

| Variable | Purpose | Vercel | .env.local | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `SECRETS_API_KEY` | Bearer token for /api/secrets/* | Manual | Via `env-pull` | Machine access (n8n, scripts) |
| `N8N_API_URL` | n8n base URL | Manual | Via `env-pull` | `https://n8n.paperworklabs.com` |
| `N8N_API_KEY` | n8n REST API key | Manual | Via `env-pull` | JWT from n8n user management |
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | GitHub API for PR list, CI status | Manual | Via `env-pull` | Fine-grained PAT with repo:read |
| `SLACK_BOT_TOKEN` | Slack API for ops page | Manual | Via `env-pull` | Bot User OAuth Token |
| `VERCEL_API_TOKEN` | Vercel API for infra checks | Manual | Via `env-pull` | NOT `VERCEL_TOKEN` (reserved) |
| `RENDER_API_KEY` | Render API for infra checks | Manual | Via `env-pull` | |
| `NEON_API_KEY` | Neon API for infra checks | Manual | Via `env-pull` | |
| `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` | Upstash health check | Manual | Via `env-pull` | |
| `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN` | Upstash health check | Manual | Via `env-pull` | |

### Optional

| Variable | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `POSTIZ_URL` | Defaults to `https://social.paperworklabs.com` |
| `N8N_BASIC_AUTH_USER` / `N8N_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD` | Alternative to N8N_API_KEY |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY` / `NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST` | PostHog analytics |
| `POSTHOG_DASHBOARD_URL` | Embedded analytics dashboards |

## Hetzner / n8n Environment Variables

### Required in compose.yaml `environment:` section

| Variable | Source in .env | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | `${GITHUB_PAT:-}` | Code nodes: GitHub API for doc fetch, PR merge |
| `SLACK_BOT_TOKEN` | `${SLACK_BOT_TOKEN:-}` | Code nodes + HTTP nodes: Slack API |
| `N8N_API_KEY` | `${N8N_API_KEY:-}` | Code nodes: n8n REST API for health checks |
| `SLACK_ALERTS_WEBHOOK_URL` | `${SLACK_ALERTS_WEBHOOK_URL:-}` | Deploy script notifications |

### Required in Hetzner .env (but NOT mapped to container)

| Variable | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Configured in n8n UI as a credential, not an env var |

## Agent Capabilities

| Capability | How |
|---|---|
| List Vercel env vars | `vercel env ls production` (CLI, project linked at `apps/studio/.vercel/project.json`) |
| Pull Vercel env to local | `make env-pull` → `vercel env pull .env.local --environment=production` |
| Validate all environments | `make env-check` → `scripts/env-check.sh` |
| SSH to Hetzner | `ssh root@204.168.147.100` (key-based auth) |
| Check n8n container env | `ssh root@204.168.147.100 "docker exec paperwork-ops-n8n-1 printenv"` |
| Restart n8n | `ssh root@204.168.147.100 "cd /opt/paperwork-ops && docker compose restart n8n"` |
| Deploy workflows | Merge to main triggers `.github/workflows/deploy-n8n.yaml`, or manual SSH deploy |

## When Adding a New Environment Variable

1. Add to the appropriate app's `.env.example` with a comment
2. Set in Vercel Dashboard (or `vercel env add`)
3. Run `make env-pull` to sync to `.env.local`
4. If needed by n8n: add to `infra/hetzner/compose.yaml` environment section AND `infra/hetzner/env.example`
5. If needed on Hetzner: SSH and add to `/opt/paperwork-ops/.env`, then `docker compose restart n8n`
6. Update this rule's inventory tables
7. Run `make env-check` to verify everything is consistent

## Known Exceptions

- `OPENAI_API_KEY`: Used by n8n but configured as an n8n UI credential, not an env var in compose.yaml
- `NODE_ENV`: Auto-set by Next.js, never manually configured
- `DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED`: Auto-provisioned by Vercel/Neon integration alongside `DATABASE_URL`; code checks both as fallback
- Temporal DB credentials (`temporal/temporal`): Hardcoded in compose.yaml, local-only service
